<title>POLAND: NBP OFFERS TO DRAIN PLN 300 MLN FOR 14 DAYS,.</title>
<headline>NBP OFFERS TO DRAIN PLN 300 MLN FOR 14 DAYS,.</headline>
<dateline>WARSAW 1997-01-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>The National Bank of Poland</p>
<p>offered to drain 300 million zlotys, in nominal terms, off the</p>
<p>market for 14 days through a reverse NBP-bill repurchase</p>
<p>auction, the bank said.</p>
<p>    Deadline hour		 - 12:00</p>
<p>    Date of settlement	  - 06 Jan 97</p>
<p>    Repurchase		    - 20 Jan 97</p>
<p>    Discount rate (pct)	 - 20.00</p>
<p>Maturity of bills offered - 3 Feb 97</p>
<p>The bank also offered to sell 100 million zlotys worth of</p>
<p>its 91-day NBP-bills and 300 million zlotys of its 182-day</p>
<p>bills with January 3 settlement date, maturing April 4, 1997</p>
<p>and July 4 1997.</p>
<p>-- Warsaw Newsroom +48 22 653 9700</p>
</text>
